latestPosts.caption:
Been feeling guilty for not posting sewing content for the longest time now.. lots of things happening at work and I’ve been too stressed out. I’m doing much better now. 

The birthday dress, if you’re waiting for it, is still a work in progress. I could have completed it simply, but I’ve been hand sewing every single bead by hand (there are LOTS of beads ). I’m nowhere close to completing it but the output I know will be worth the wait. Quality over quantity always.

My life right now is at the crossroads with everything happening at once( life’s cliche of course - all or nothing ) but hopefully it’ll all settle down soon and I can come back to your regularly scheduled program at Azarel. 

Went to my friend’s wedding and would you believe me if I said I shopped this saree in 5 mins. Richard dared me to pick the first saree I saw and I did ! Turned out so good. 
 
So here’s a little dare for you. When too many things happening for you and you feel like you can’t handle it all, make quick decisions about the petty things, take time for yourself and take things slow. The world can wait. 

Thanks for waiting. Lots of love to you ❤️

Would you want to see the slow progress of the birthday dress as it happens or do you want a big final reveal?

Your everyday sunscreen step just got a major upgrade and Iniya’s here to tell you why it’s time to make the switch. Whether you’re heading to work, brunch, or just chilling at home, this is the sunscreen step you’ll actually look forward to. Watch Iniya break down why TINTENSE is your new go-to- and why your skin will thank you 💛

Feeling CHOSEN – Iniya's Journey with the Community

For Iniya, CHOSEN is more than just skincare—it’s about belonging. From the very beginning, she felt like she was part of something bigger. Events like the conclave have only deepened that connection, strengthening her bond with the community.

"It encourages me when a brand makes me feel like a person."

What sets CHOSEN apart? The way it fosters real conversations. Iniya loves reading others' experiences on social media, gaining insights that help her make better choices. But her most meaningful experience? The beach cleanup event, where she saw firsthand how much people truly love and believe in the brand.

For Iniya, community events bring people closer, creating an intimacy with CHOSEN that goes beyond products. And if she had to describe CHOSEN in one word?

"Chosen."

Because that’s exactly how the brand makes her feel—seen, valued, and truly part of something special.

latestPosts.caption:
SPF clothing to me means denim! While other fabrics lose their sun protection abilities due to repeated washing, stretch or sweat, denim endures. That’s why when I got to know that @a_z_a_r_e_l loves to play with this difficult fabric for her label, I requested her to make me a denim poncho. And how she delivered - she made a super stylish, double sided, absolutely sun proof cape, that goes with a lot of outfits and is potentially durable forever! 
Requested her to custom make this for a few of our patients who have photosensitivity related pigmentation issues, and see that making a big impact in the future. Right now, she’s available to custom make it on request, but hopefully over time, we can see this in CHOSEN store and in mainstream stores everywhere else too! You go girl @a_z_a_r_e_l
